<task id="task_lyr_vqg_pvb">
    <title>Getting the Latest License File from <ph
            conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/></title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>When you use a license file for activating certain agents with the installer package
                downloaded from <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/>, if a
                license expiration error message appears, follow the instructions below to get the
                latest license file and PSN (Product Serial Number) from <ph
                    conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/>.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>To get the latest license file, go to <ph
                        conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/>
                    <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>License</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Download the latest license file</uicontrol> at the bottom of
                    the <wintitle>License</wintitle> page.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <fig id="fig_zkp_5rx_wvb">
                        <title>Download lLcense File from <ph
                                conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/></title>
                        <image href="../images/download_license_file_from_s1=20221219234340.png"
                            id="image_ysy_5rx_wvb"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>The license file (a <filepath>.txt</filepath> file) has been downloaded to your
                    Downloads folder.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>To get the PSN, go to <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/>
                    <uicontrol>About</uicontrol> page.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Find and copy the product serial number.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <fig id="fig_eqd_nk2_tvb">
                        <title>Get Product Serial Number from <ph
                                conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SERVER_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"/></title>
                        <image
                            href="../images/psn_stellarone=20221206143840.png"
                            id="image_osg_4k2_tvb"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
